<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE4DFF9E6BDCD499FEBAF3A8" blockId="11.[151,1436,1497,2026]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,152,603]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Herb, basal parts unknown. Synflorescence 5–7-nodate with 13–40 florescences, lowermost node with a welldeveloped leaf, each subsequent node with a bladeless sheath, first internode 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996F18D740FB2DF54D" box="[1107,1221,1536,1562]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="2.1" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="1.0">1–3.2 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle ± glabrous. Leaf at lowermost node with sheath 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996983D766FCCCF517" box="[712,804,1574,1600]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="7.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="5.0">5–9 cm</quantity>
, puberulent along margins; petiole 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996F9BD766FABEF517" box="[1232,1366,1574,1600]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.9 cm</quantity>
long, glabrous; pulvinus 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996A3CD70DFE12F530" box="[375,506,1613,1639]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="2.3">2.3–3.8 cm</quantity>
long, laterally ± flattened, puberulent adaxially, usually without annulus; blade ovate, ± coriaceous when dry, base truncate, apex acute to acuminate, oblique (apex displacement 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996E09D734FF57F5E3" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="2.55" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3.3 cm</quantity>
), 26–50 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996A77D7DAFE5BF5E3" box="[316,435,1690,1716]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11–15 cm</quantity>
, length from base to broadest part 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996800D7DAFC2BF5E3" box="[843,963,1690,1716]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 cm</quantity>
, adaxial surface not papillose, hirtellous to puberulent along midrib and at apex, abaxial surface not papillose, hirtellous at apex. Main florescence 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996E22D781FF08F455" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="6.75" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5– 10 cm</quantity>
long, with 5–16 ± distichous to unilaterally arranged bracts, first internode 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996F29D7A8FB0EF455" box="[1122,1254,1768,1794]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.9 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996BDCD64EFEF2F47F" box="[151,282,1806,1832]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.1 cm</quantity>
long; lowermost bract 1.9–2.2 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF9969D7D64EFCCAF47F" box="[668,802,1806,1832]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.1 cm</quantity>
, reddish, glabrous or puberulent at apex; first prophyll 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996BDCD675FEC4F418" box="[151,300,1845,1871]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.375" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="13.75" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.5">12.5–15 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; rarely with an interphyll ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF99687DD675FC77F418" box="[822,927,1845,1871]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
long. Flowers 3–4 per bract; pedicel 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996E11D675FF2DF421" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
long; ovary ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996A35D61CFE2AF421" box="[382,450,1884,1910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, puberulent apically; sepals 10–11.5 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996885D61CFBDCF421" box="[974,1076,1884,1910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, apex obtuse; corolla tube 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996E3BD61CFF02F4CB" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="19.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="18.0">18– 20 mm</quantity>
long, outside glabrous, inside hirsute in mouth, lobes ca 5 × 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996889D6C2FBD6F4CB" box="[962,1086,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4 mm</quantity>
, only slightly open, leaving a small pore at apex; outer staminode absent; stamen 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF9969B0D6E9FCB4F494" box="[763,860,1961,1987]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
long, appendage tapering to base of theca, theca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996BDCD690FEE4F4BD" box="[151,268,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long; callose staminode 3.5–4 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF9969E6D690FD1CF4BD" box="[685,756,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
, with a shelf-shaped callus at ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4DFF996F24D690FB5AF4BD" box="[1135,1202,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
from apex, petaloid appendage absent; cucullate staminode 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E692DD1D8FD2FF3E5" box="[614,711,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, lateral appendage ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6F4CD1D8FBA2F3E5" box="[1031,1098,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long; style 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6F9FD1D8FA89F3E5" box="[1236,1377,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3.5 mm</quantity>
long (tripped). Capsule 17–18 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6959D1FEFD9CF38F" box="[530,628,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
; seed ca 14.5 × ca 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6829D1FEFC44F38F" box="[866,940,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
; aril 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E68A6D1FEFB81F38F" box="[1005,1129,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, with two flattened unilateral lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE4AFF9E6B8DD04BFDB5F21B" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE4AFF9E6B8DD04BFDB5F21B" blockId="12.[151,1436,152,603]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E6B8DD04BFE14F272" bold="true" box="[198,508,267,293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Known only from the coastal cordillera of northern 
<collectingCountry id="C6B57634EE4AFF9E6FDFD04CFAE7F271" box="[1172,1295,268,294]" name="Venezuela" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, where it is found at an elevation of about 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6AB6D072FDB0F21B" box="[509,600,306,332]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE4AFF9E6B8DD018FA83F10C" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE4AFF9E6B8DD018FDEEF163" blockId="12.[151,1436,152,603]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E6B8DD018FEA2F225" bold="true" box="[198,330,344,370]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E6A24D019FD54F225" box="[367,700,345,370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionale">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E6A24D019FD54F225" box="[367,700,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Monotagma septentrionale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E68DDD019FEDEF2CE" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E68DDD019FB96F225" authorityName="Loesener" authorityYear="1915" box="[918,1150,345,370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustissimum">M. angustissimum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E6FD1D019FA88F225" authorityName="Schumann" authorityYear="1902" baseAuthorityName="Koernicke" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1178,1376,345,370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="densiflorum">M. densiflorum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E6E37D019FEDEF2CE" authorityName="Steyermark &amp; Bunting" authorityYear="1973" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yapacanensis">M. yapacanensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E6A32D0C0FDCCF2CE" box="[377,548,384,409]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E6A32D0C0FDCCF2CE" box="[377,548,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. papillosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having reddish bracts and the lowermost synflorescence node provided with a leaf blade. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4AFF9E6971D0E7FCF5F297" authorityName="Loesener" authorityYear="1915" box="[570,797,423,448]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustissimum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4AFF9E6971D0E7FCF5F297" box="[570,797,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. angustissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having spreading basal leaf sheaths (vs. tightly imbricate) and a glabrous or slightly puberulent synflorescence peduncle (vs. lanate). It differs from the other three species in having strongly oblique leaf apices (apex displacement 1.8–4.5 vs. 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6FDDD0B4FAE1F159" box="[1174,1289,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.0">0–1.5 cm</quantity>
) and longer sepals (10–11.5 vs. 
<quantity id="795A9B41EE4AFF9E6A35D35AFE12F163" box="[382,506,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="6.25" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="3.0">3–9.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
